title: Dr. & Mrs. Gilbert Grosvenor, Washington D.C.

thumbnail.alt_text: A work made of platinum-palladium print.

inscriptions: Inscribed verso: “DR. AND MRS. GILBERT H. GROSVENOR / (WASHINGTON, D.C., 1951) [in a box]”; inscribed verso: “.. / P1033 / .. [in a circle]”; inscribed verso: “GROSVENORS / Platinum-palladium / Print made 1973 / Arches Paper / Single coating, multiple printing”; inscribed verso: “24/35”; signed and stamped verso: “Irving Penn / IRVING PENN [in a circle]”; stamped and inscribed verso: “PHOTOGRAPH BY IRVING PENN / Copyright © 1951–RENEWED 1979 by / THE CONDE NAST PUBLICATIONS INC. / Not to be reproduced without / written permission of the / copyright owner.”; stamped and inscribed verso: “Hand-coated by the photographer / I.P.”
publication_history:
Penn, Irving. 1960. “Moments Preserved.” Simon and Schuster. p. 114. (other print of this image)

Galleria Civica d’Arte Moderna, Turin. 1975. “I platini di Irving Penn: 25 anni di fotografia.” Exh. cat. Galleria Civica d’Arte Moderna/Ages Arti Grafiche. p. 22. (other print of this image)

Szarkowski, John. 1984. "Irving Penn." Exh. cat. Museum of Modern Art/New York Graphic Society Books. pl. 33. (other print of this image)

Penn, Irving. 1991. “Passage: A Work Record.” Knopf. p. 113. (other print of this image)

Westerbeck, Colin. 1997. “Irving Penn: A Career in Photography.” Exh. cat. Art Institute of Chicago/Bulfinch Press. p. 146, cat. 79, pl. 79.

Greenough, Sarah. 2005. “Irving Penn: Platinum Prints.” Exh. cat. National Gallery of Art/Yale University Press. pl. 34. (other print of this image)
exhibition_history: Art Institute of Chicago, “Irving Penn, A Career in Photography,” November 22, 1997–February 1, 1998; traveled to St. Petersburg, Russia, State Hermitage Museum, March 1–May 16, 1998; Hamburg, Germany, Deichtorhallen, June 18–September 6, 1998; Munich, Germany, Müchner Stadtmuseum, October 6, 1998–February 21, 1999; San Francisco, California, Friends of Photography/Ansel Adams Center for Photography, November 11, 1999–January 23, 2000; Museum of Fine Arts, Houston, March 25–June 4, 2000; Paris, France, Maison Européenne de la Photographie, September 13–November 5, 2000. (Colin Westerbeck)
provenance_text: Given by the artist to the Art Institute, 1996.
